<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-13T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-13T05:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/731</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-13T10:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 14, 2.50
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1234. Referring to the Embassy’s telegram 1206, April 5, 7 p.m., for
                                War Trade Board, No. 14 from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>.<note n="1" xml:id="d722fn1">Not printed.</note> Not having yet
                                secured single permit to export to A[merican] E[xpeditionary]
                                F[orces] under terms of commercial agreement March 7, Embassy
                                ventures to request authority to inform Minister of Foreign Affairs,
                                that Board will grant no more licenses to export trade to Spain,
                                until Spanish Government shall have granted permits to export to <pb facs="0842" n="1676" xml:id="pg_1676"/> A.E.F. those articles
                                covered by agreement of March 7 for which application has already
                                been made and to suggest that Spanish Ambassador at Washington be
                                similarly informed. Embassy ventures further to suggest authority to
                                remind Foreign Office that Board is free after May 7 to impose such
                                bunker regulations as it may see fit on Spanish vessels in American
                                waters.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>